The paper discusses algorithmic fairness, which is a topic that falls under the broad categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces the concept of a construct space, which is related to the idea of hidden variables in statistics and could be relevant to the subfield of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the assumptions that different mechanisms for fairness require, which could be relevant to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
